    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.77/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-16T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 16, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 17—7:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1164. My 737, July [<hi rend="italic">June</hi>] 16, 4 p.m. for Feis. Delighted
                    to learn of orders placed for rolling stock for Egypt. Be sure not to forget
                    necessity for sending transportation experts and the sooner the better.
                    Greetings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
